{{notability|Books|date=July 2018}} '''88 Precepts''' is an essay or manifesto written by [[David Lane (white supremacist)|David Lane]], a member of the [[white supremacy|white supremacist]] organization [[The Order (white supremacist group)|The Order]]. Written while Lane was serving a 190-year prison sentence, 88 Precepts is a treatise on [[natural law]], [[religion]], race and politics from the view point of David Lane including instructions for securing, protecting, preserving and establishing white [[Northwest Territorial Imperative|territorial imperatives]] in the [[Northwestern United States]] and [[Eastern Europe]], distributing [[propaganda]]<ref>{{Citation | last = Anti-Defamation League | first = | title = David Lane | url=http://www.adl.org/learn/ext_us/lane.asp?xpicked=2&item=lane | accessdate = 2007-09-29}}</ref> and are an expansion upon Lane's [[Fourteen Words]] and religion of [[Wotansvolk|Wotanism]]. The 88 Precepts are commonly regarded as "tenets of white-separatist life" used by white supremacy groups and those who advocate [[white nationalism]] and [[White separatism|separatism]]. Lane was heavily critical of democracy, multiculturalism and [[racial integration]]. The 88 Precepts further elaborate on Lane's [[White genocide conspiracy theory]]. <ref>{{Citation | last = Rider | first = Sarah | title = Tolerating Intolerance: Resisting the Urge to Silence Student Opinion in the Writing Classroom | url=http://www.nwp.org/cs/public/print/resource/531 | accessdate = 2007-09-29}}</ref>
Lane claimed that 14-88 was an integral part of his ''Pyramid Prophecy''<ref>https://books.google.com/books?id=FIwwWSSL5JIC&pg=PA381</ref> and the fundamental doctrine in his religion of [[Wotansvolk|Wotanism]]. 1488 is a combination of 14 as in Lane's [[14 Words]] and [[88 (number)#In_white_nationalism|88]], a white nationalist/supremacist slogan for "Heil Hitler"<ref>1488 is a combination of two popular white supremacist numeric symbols. The first symbol is 14, which is shorthand for the "14 Words" slogan http://www.adl.org/combating-hate/hate-on-display/c/1488.html</ref>
